The article is a presidential memorandum from January 13, 2017, regarding the order of succession within the Council on Environmental Quality. The memorandum outlines the officials who will act as the Chairman of the Council on Environmental Quality in the event that the Chairman is unable to perform their duties. It also specifies exceptions and revokes a previous memorandum on the same subject. The memorandum concludes with general provisions and authorizes publication in the Federal Register. The memorandum was issued by President Barack Obama.